From: WaveCrux Pro capture pipeline
Subject: [PATCH] cocotb 2.0 compat + 1 GbE-only trim for eth_mac_1g_rgmii

Two changes to Forencich's `test_eth_mac_1g_rgmii.py`, applied as a
single patch by the capture pipeline:

1. **cocotb 2.0 compatibility.** The upstream testbench predates the
   cocotb 2.0 LogicArray/Logic API change. Three patterns break under
   cocotb 2.0.1:
     - `assert dut.speed == N` — comparing a `LogicArrayObject` to an
       `int` no longer works implicitly; cast through `.value` and
       `int()`.
     - `dut.mac_gmii_tx_clk_en.value.integer` — single-bit `Logic`
       objects no longer expose `.integer`; use `int(.value)`.
   The upstream verilog-ethernet repo was marked **deprecated** on
   2025-02-27 and will not receive these fixes. We patch locally.

2. **Trim the test sweep to 1 GbE only.** The full sweep runs each of
   `run_test_rx`, `run_test_tx`, `run_test_tx_underrun`, `run_test_tx_error`
   at three link speeds (1 Gbit, 100 Mbit, 10 Mbit). At 10 Mbit the clock
   period is 50× longer than at 1 GbE, so the 10/100 Mbit cases dominate
   sim time and FST size. The decoder treats all three speeds identically
   (one byte per full clock cycle on a DDR data bus); the 1 GbE case
   covers the decode path. We also trim `size_list` from 80 frames to 12
   frames (60..69 + 512 + 1514) — enough to exercise small/mid/jumbo
   without redundant runt repetition. Net: FST shrinks from ~50 MB
   (estimated, all-speeds-all-sizes) to 52 KB.

Apply with `patch -p1` from inside `verilog-ethernet/tb/eth_mac_1g_rgmii/`:

    patch -p1 < forencich_eth_mac_1g_rgmii_cocotb2_1gbe.patch

Tested against `alexforencich/verilog-ethernet` commit
`77320a9471d19c7dd383914bc049e02d9f4f1ffb`.

